Notes: Associating 'row_id' with the 'hasCode' property of DrugPrescription captures its identifier within the prescription context, which is semantically meaningful.
The 'patient_id' directly relates to the 'hasPatient' relationship, linking the prescription to the patient entity.
The ATC code indicates the drug involved, which is linked via the 'hasDrug' relationship.
Diagnosis code provides indication to start medication, linked via 'hasIndicationToStart' to Diagnosis.
The creation date directly maps to the 'hasDateTime' property with appropriate datatype.
Number of times per day relates to frequency, mapped via 'hasFrequency'.
Dosage details are linked to the drug entity; specific dosage data can be captured as an annotation or attribute.
